# VERSION
1.10.0

# Changelog
- 1.10.0
    - **Data Catalog API** — comprehensive data asset discovery and metadata service
        - New endpoint: `GET /api/v2/catalog/overview` — aggregate stats: total tables, rows, disk usage, per-domain and per-storage-tier breakdown
        - New endpoint: `GET /api/v2/catalog/tables` — list all tables with row counts, sizes, time ranges, storage tier; supports `?domain=` filter
        - New endpoint: `GET /api/v2/catalog/tables/{schema}/{table}` — table detail: column metadata, JSONB key discovery, index info, data lineage
        - New endpoint: `GET /api/v2/catalog/storage` — tablespace-level storage info (NVMe vs SATA distribution)
        - New endpoint: `GET /api/v2/catalog/graph` — Neo4j graph catalog: available flag, node labels, relationship types, total nodes/edges
        - All endpoints support `?refresh=true` to bypass 5-minute in-memory cache
        - New `CatalogDao`: queries PostgreSQL system catalogs (`pg_class`, `pg_stat_user_tables`, `information_schema`, `pg_tablespace`) with TimescaleDB hypertable detection (graceful fallback when not installed)
        - SQL injection protection: identifier validation via regex for dynamic column/table names in `GetTimeRange`
        - New `CatalogService`: merges dynamic DB metadata with static registry of table descriptions, column descriptions, domain classifications, and data lineage info; supports factor/regime domains for future tables and Neo4j graph metadata observation
        - 5-minute in-memory cache with `sync.RWMutex` for table listing (avoids repeated `pg_total_relation_size` calls)
        - Reuses existing `SchemaDao` for JSONB key introspection (no duplication)
        - New `CatalogController`: 5 HTTP handlers with standard error responses
        - New constants: `COMP_DAO_CATALOG`, `COMP_SVC_CATALOG`, `COMP_CTRL_CATALOG`
        - New model structs: `CatalogOverview`, `TableCatalogEntry`, `TableDetail`, `ColumnMeta`, `IndexMeta`, `DataLineage`, `StorageInfo`, `TablespaceInfo`, `GraphCatalogOverview`, `GraphLabelInfo`, `GraphRelTypeInfo`, etc.
        - Exported `dao.HumanSize()` utility for human-readable byte formatting
    - **Storage Tier Planning** — new documentation
        - `docs/2026-05-09 STORAGE_TIER_PLANNING.md`: complete table-to-storage mapping based on 372+ planned factors, revised data volume estimates, and "avoid migration" principle
        - Core strategy: NVMe only for PGVector KNN + metadata (<100 GB); all business data (bars, factors, strategy, financial) on 8TB SATA SSD from day one
        - TimescaleDB hypertable + compression planning for all time-series tables
    - **PostgreSQL storage-tier migration SQL**
        - `migrations/postgresql/security/0001_security_init.sql`: now places small metadata tables on `pg_default` and industry tables on `warm_storage` at creation time
        - `migrations/postgresql/security/0002_financial_data.sql`: now places financial tables and indexes on `warm_storage` at creation time
        - `migrations/postgresql/security/0003_industry_date_columns.sql`: recreated indexes now stay on `warm_storage`
        - `migrations/postgresql/kg/0001_kg_init.sql`: now places KG metadata tables on `pg_default` and large JSONB tables on `warm_storage`
        - `migrations/postgresql/security/0004_storage_tier_setup.sql`: legacy backfill migration for existing deployments; explicitly documents that hot/warm is controlled by PostgreSQL `TABLESPACE`, not `config.yaml`
    - **Data Catalog Design** — new documentation
        - `docs/2026-05-09 DATA_CATALOG_DESIGN.md`: API contracts, data models, architecture, Cthulhu dashboard wireframes, Neo4j graph catalog support
    - **Unit Tests** — catalog model/DAO/service coverage
        - `model/catalog_test.go`: JSON serialization tests for all catalog model structs (CatalogOverview, TableCatalogEntry, TableDetail, StorageInfo), omitempty validation
        - `dao/catalog_dao_test.go`: `HumanSize` formatting, SQL identifier safety regex
        - `service/catalog_service_test.go`: static metadata registry (exact match, prefix match, priority, fallback), column descriptions, lineage, time columns, domain completeness

- v1.9.1
    - Removed toolchain from go.mod to allow users to use their preferred Go version (e.g., 1.23+).
- v1.9.0
    - **Industry data fixes — trade_date DATE type + taxonomy_security_map auto-sync**
        - Migration `0003_industry_date_columns.sql`: `trade_date` column changed from `VARCHAR(10)` to native `DATE` type in `industry_weight` and `industry_daily` tables; dependent indexes and unique constraints rebuilt
        - `IndustryWeight.TradeDate` / `IndustryDaily.TradeDate`: GORM tag updated from `type:varchar(10)` to `type:date` (matches existing `StandardBar` pattern)
        - Defense-in-depth: `BatchUpsertWeights` and `BatchUpsertIndustryDaily` controllers now normalize incoming `trade_date` via `normalizeDateYYYYMMDD()` before DB write
        - New endpoint: `POST /api/v2/taxonomy/{source}/{taxonomy}/{market}/mapping/sync_from_constituents` — derives `taxonomy_security_map` entries by JOINing `industry_constituent` with `taxonomy_category` on `index_code`; uses `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`
        - `TaxonomyDao.SyncMappingsFromConstituents()`: raw SQL INSERT…SELECT with DISTINCT + JOIN + ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING
        - `TaxonomyService.SyncMappingsFromConstituents()`: validation + logging
    - **Write Buffer V2 — generic multi-business-type buffer**
        - Refactored `WriteBufferManager` from bars-only to generic multi-type architecture
        - New `genericBuffer` replaces `tableBuffer`: accepts typed `FlushFunc` per buffer key, decoupled from specific DAOs
        - New business types supported: `industry_weight`, `industry_daily` (bars preserved as `bars` category)
        - `WriteBufferManager` now injects `TaxonomyDao` alongside `BarsDao`
        - `BufferStats` gains `category` field — each buffer reports its business type (bars/industry_weight/industry_daily)
        - `TaxonomyController` now routes weight and daily upserts through the write buffer for small batches (< direct_flush_threshold), direct write for large batches
        - `TaxonomyController` depends on `BufferManager` interface for testability
        - Bars ext flush fixed: `barsEntry` now carries the `Query` reference, restoring `BatchUpsertExt` functionality that was lost in the generic refactor
        - `/api/v2/buffer/stats` response now includes `category` per buffer for frontend categorization

- v1.8.0
    - **Knowledge Graph (KG) Domain** — data persistence layer for Atlas KG Engine
        - New PostgreSQL schema: `kg` with 6 tables (documents, extractions, events, graph_ingestions, daily_runs, impact_logs)
        - New `kg.events` table: normalized/deduplicated event store with fingerprint-based identity
            - Columns: event_fingerprint, entity_name, event_type, direction, time_bucket, severity, source_doc_ids[], source_count
            - Supports event merging: when duplicate event arrives, source_doc_ids and source_count are updated
        - Updated `kg.documents`: added `source_type` column (graph_building vs event_triggering)
        - Updated `kg.daily_runs`: new columns for docs_graph_building, docs_event, events_new, events_deduped
        - Updated `kg.impact_logs`: added `event_id` FK linking to normalized events
        - New model: `KgDocument`, `KgExtraction`, `KgEvent`, `KgGraphIngestion`, `KgDailyRun`, `KgImpactLog` with GORM tags
        - New custom types: `StringArray` (PostgreSQL TEXT[]), `JSONB` (PostgreSQL JSONB) with Scanner/Valuer
        - New DAO: `KgDao` — unified DAO for all 6 kg tables with filter structs
        - New Service: `KgService` — thin business logic layer wrapping DAO
        - New Controller: `KgController` — 17 HTTP endpoints:
            - Documents: POST/GET/GET/{id}/PUT
            - Extractions: POST/GET/GET/{id}
            - Events: POST/GET/GET/{id}/PUT + GET /recent
            - Graph Ingestions: POST
            - Daily Runs: POST/GET
            - Impact Logs: POST/GET
        - Routes registered at `/api/v1/kg/*`
        - New constants: COMP_DAO_KG, COMP_SVC_KG, COMP_CTRL_KG, DB_PG_KG
        - Updated migration: `migrations/postgresql/kg/0001_kg_init.sql`
    - **Graph API (Neo4j)** — HTTP proxy to Neo4j graph database for Atlas
        - Integrates Neo4j infra component (v0.18.0) into PhoenixA
        - New DAO: `GraphDao` — wraps Neo4j component with typed query methods
            - `MergeNode`, `MergeEdge` — idempotent MERGE operations
            - `SearchNodes`, `GetCompanyFull`, `GetCompanyChain` — graph traversal queries
            - `GetCompanyTimeline`, `GetCompetitors`, `GetEventImpacts` — specialized reads
            - `GetGraphStats` — node/edge count aggregation
            - `EnsureSchema` — create constraints and indexes
            - `GetResourceRelatedCompanies` — for impact analysis
        - New Service: `GraphService` — thin wrapper with logging
        - New Controller: `GraphController` — 14 HTTP endpoints:
            - `POST /api/v1/graph/cypher` — read-only Cypher execution
            - `POST /api/v1/graph/cypher/write` — write Cypher execution
            - `POST /api/v1/graph/nodes/merge` + `/merge-batch` — node merge (single + batch)
            - `POST /api/v1/graph/edges/merge` + `/merge-batch` — edge merge (single + batch)
            - `GET /api/v1/graph/search?q=...` — full-text node search
            - `GET /api/v1/graph/company/{name}` — company + all relationships
            - `GET /api/v1/graph/company/{name}/chain` — supply chain BFS
            - `GET /api/v1/graph/company/{name}/timeline` — time-ordered events
            - `GET /api/v1/graph/company/{name}/competitors` — competitor list
            - `GET /api/v1/graph/event/{name}/impacts` — event impact on companies
            - `GET /api/v1/graph/stats` — graph statistics
            - `POST /api/v1/graph/schema/ensure` — create constraints/indexes
        - Graph API conditionally registered (only when `neo4j.enabled: true`)
        - Neo4j config section added to `config.yaml`
        - New constants: COMP_DAO_GRAPH, COMP_SVC_GRAPH, COMP_CTRL_GRAPH
- v1.7.0
    - **Write Buffer** — in-process batch write optimization for high-frequency small upserts
        - New component: `WriteBufferManager` (`internal/buffer/write_buffer.go`)
            - Per-table channel + goroutine architecture (lazy-created per buffer key)
            - Flush triggers: batch full (2000 rows) / interval (configurable) / graceful shutdown
            - Bars + ext data bundled in single submission, flushed atomically
            - Non-blocking submit with 503 backpressure when channel full
        - `BarsController.Upsert()` routing logic:
            - `len(bars) >= direct_flush_threshold (500)` → bypass buffer, direct DB write (full-load path)
            - `len(bars) < 500` → submit to write buffer (daily-update path)
        - New endpoint: `GET /api/v2/buffer/stats` — per-buffer metrics (submitted/flushed/pending/flush_count)
        - New biz_config section: `write_buffer` (enabled, max_batch_size, flush_interval, direct_flush_threshold, channel_size, shutdown_timeout)
        - New `internal/config/config.go` — PhoenixA BizConfig + `SetBizConfig` init
        - Unit tests: 6 test cases covering disabled/interval-flush/batch-full/channel-full/ext-bundled/multi-key
        - Design doc: `docs/2026-05-07 DESIGN_BATCH_WRITE_BUFFER.md`
- v1.6.0
    - **PostgreSQL Migration Phase 2** — financial_statement & corporate_action tables migrated to PostgreSQL
        - `FinancialStatementDao` and `CorporateActionDao` switched from `mysql_gorm` to `postgres_gorm`
        - `SchemaDao` switched to `postgres_gorm`; JSON queries rewritten: `JSON_TABLE`/`JSON_KEYS` → `LATERAL jsonb_object_keys()`
        - New PostgreSQL migration: `migrations/postgresql/security/0002_financial_data.sql`
            - 2 tables: `financial_statement`, `corporate_action` with PG-native types
            - JSONB GIN indexes (`jsonb_path_ops`): `idx_fs_data_gin`, `idx_ca_data_gin`
            - Partial indexes on `ann_date` and `comp_type_code`
        - **JSONB query capabilities**:
            - `FinancialStatementFilters` / `CorporateActionFilters`: new `DataContains` (`@>`) and `DataHasKey` (`?`) fields
            - Enables queries like: `WHERE data_json @> '{"TOTAL_ASSETS": 100000000}'`
        - Model updates: `type:json` → `type:jsonb`, `int` → `smallint` for `comp_type_code`
        - Bug fix: `_int()` in Artemis `base_financial_statement.py` — `int(float(val))` for `COMP_TYPE_CODE` type inconsistency
        - New doc: `2026-05-07 FINANCIAL_DATA_PG_MIGRATION.md`
        - Upgrade infra to v0.17.2 to support latest `postgres_gorm` features.
- v1.5.0
    - **PostgreSQL Migration Phase 1** — taxonomy & industry tables migrated to PostgreSQL
        - **Only TaxonomyDao** switched from `mysql_gorm` to `postgres_gorm`
        - All other DAOs (security, bars, strategy_run, financial_statement, corporate_action, schema) remain on MySQL
        - New PostgreSQL migration: `migrations/postgresql/security/0001_security_init.sql`
            - 5 tables: taxonomy_category, taxonomy_security_map, industry_constituent, industry_weight, industry_daily
            - PG-native types: BIGSERIAL, BOOLEAN, JSONB, TIMESTAMPTZ, NUMERIC
        - **JSONB advantages leveraged**:
            - `taxonomy_category.attrs_json` uses JSONB with GIN index (`idx_tc_attrs_gin`)
            - Enables fast `@>` containment queries: e.g. `WHERE attrs_json @> '{"is_pub": 1}'`
            - Enables `?` key-existence queries: e.g. `WHERE attrs_json ? 'change_reason'`
            - `TaxonomyCategoryFilters` gains `AttrsContains` and `AttrsHasKey` fields
        - `config.yaml`: added `postgres_gorm.data_sources.security` (schema: `security_dev`)
        - `mysql_gorm` kept enabled — all non-taxonomy DAOs still read/write MySQL
        - Taxonomy model updated: `tinyint unsigned` → `smallint`, `tinyint(1)` → `boolean`, `json` → `jsonb`
- v1.4.0
    - **Taxonomy V2** — multi-taxonomy, multi-market support for industry data
        - New fields: `taxonomy` (swhy/citic/gics/concept/region/mairui) and `market` (zh_a/us/jp/hk) on all taxonomy/industry tables
        - `taxonomy_category`: added `index_code` field (行业指数代码, separated from attrs_json)
        - `industry_constituent` / `industry_weight`: added `symbol` field (pure code, joins security_registry); `con_code` retained as raw SDK value
        - Route pattern changed: `/api/v2/taxonomy/{source}/{taxonomy}/{market}/...`
        - Breaking: old `/api/v2/taxonomy/{source}/...` routes still work but taxonomy/market default to empty
        - New migration: `0002_taxonomy_v2.sql` — DROP + recreate all taxonomy/industry tables
        - Updated model, DAO, service, controller for taxonomy+market dimensions
- v1.3.2
    - Adjusted folder structure of migration, postgresql migration supported.
- v1.3.1
    - **Bug Fixes**:
        - [Critical] Fixed `data_json` double-encoding: `FinancialStatement.DataJSON` and `CorporateAction.DataJSON` changed from `string` to `json.RawMessage` — API responses now return proper nested JSON objects instead of escaped JSON strings
        - [Medium] Fixed `SchemaDao.Overview()` missing sort — added `sort.Slice` by domain name for deterministic output
        - [Minor] Fixed `FieldsResult.SampleCount` — now returns `min(totalCount, sampleSize)` instead of always returning totalCount
        - [Minor] Fixed `SchemaDao.Overview()` silently swallowing errors from count queries and field discovery
        - [Low] Added max `page_size` cap (1000) in `FinancialStatementService` and `CorporateActionService` to prevent unbounded table scans
- v1.3.0
    - **Schema Discovery API** — dynamic field introspection for JSON-stored data
        - New endpoints:
            - `GET /api/v2/schema/domains` — list all data domains
            - `GET /api/v2/schema/types?domain=...` — list data types in a domain
            - `GET /api/v2/schema/fields?domain=...&type=...` — discover actual fields from stored data via MySQL JSON_KEYS()
            - `GET /api/v2/schema/overview` — summary of all domains with row counts and field counts
        - Uses domain allow-list for safety (prevents arbitrary table access)
        - Supports `sample_size` parameter to control query performance
        - New DAO: `SchemaDao` with `DiscoverFields()`, `ListTypes()`, `Overview()`
        - New Controller: `SchemaController`
- v1.2.0
    - Added unified financial statement support (balance sheet / income / cashflow / profit_express / profit_notice):
        - New table: `financial_statement` with JSON column for 180+ numeric fields
        - Design rationale: JSON storage avoids 180-column wide table; single table serves all statement types for extensibility
        - UNIQUE KEY on (source, symbol, market, statement_type, reporting_period, report_type, statement_code) ensures upsert idempotency
        - New model: `FinancialStatement`, `FinancialStatementFilters`
        - New DAO/Service/Controller: `FinancialStatementDao`, `FinancialStatementService`, `FinancialStatementController`
        - New API endpoints:
            - `POST /api/v2/financial/{source}/{statement_type}/upsert`
            - `GET  /api/v2/financial/{source}/{statement_type}?symbol=...&period_start=...&period_end=...`
        - Registered components: `dao_financial_stmt`, `svc_financial_stmt`, `ctrl_financial_stmt`
        - New reference constants (`internal/consts/financial.go`):
            - `FIN_STMT_*`: statement type identifiers
            - `REPORT_TYPE_*`: Q1/H1/Q3/Annual (报告期名称 1-4)
            - `STMT_CODE_*`: statement codes 1-10 (合并报表/母公司报表 variants)
            - `PROFIT_NOTICE_*`: 业绩预告类型代码 1-11
        - Updated `0001_init.sql` migration with new table definition
    - Added corporate action support (dividend / right_issue):
        - New table: `corporate_action` with JSON column for variable data fields
        - UNIQUE KEY on (source, symbol, market, action_type, report_period, ann_date) ensures upsert idempotency
        - New model/DAO/Service/Controller: `CorporateAction*`
        - New API endpoints:
            - `POST /api/v2/corporate-action/{source}/{action_type}/upsert`
            - `GET  /api/v2/corporate-action/{source}/{action_type}?symbol=...&period_start=...&period_end=...`
        - New reference constants (`internal/consts/corporate_action.go`):
            - `CORP_ACTION_*`: action type identifiers
            - `DIV_PROGRESS_*`: dividend progress codes 1-19
            - `RI_PROGRESS_*`: right issue progress codes 1-22
- v1.1.0
